{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Berisad Glacier | other_name = | photo = Sentinel-Range-location-map.png | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Sentinel Range in Western Antarctica | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Berisad Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Ellsworth Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|78|25|20|S|84|51|50|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|3|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|1|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Dater Glacier]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
[[File:Vinson-Map.jpg|thumb|280px|Sentinel Range map.]]
'''Berisad Glacier''' ({{lang-bg|text=ледник Берисад|italic=yes}}, ‘Lednik Berisad’ \'led-nik 'be-ri-sad\) is a glacier {{convert|3|nmi|0|abbr=on}} long and {{convert|1|nmi|0|abbr=on}} wide in [[Veregava Ridge]], central [[Sentinel Range]] in [[Ellsworth Mountains]], [[Antarctica]]. It flows north-northwestwards from [[Kushla Peak]] to join [[Dater Glacier]] northeast of [[Sipey Peak]].<ref>[http://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/display_name.cfm?gaz_id=137247v Berisad Glacier.] SCAR Composite Antarctic Gazetteer.</ref>
The glacier is named after the [[Kingdom of Thrace|Thracian]] King [[Berisades|Berisad]], 358-352 BC.
==Location== Berisad Glacier is centred at {{coord|78|25|20|S|84|51|50|W|display=inline,title}}. US mapping in 1961, updated in 1988.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
