{{Comoros-stub}}

'''Mariano de la Paz Graëlls y de la Aguera''' (1809 – 1898) was a Spanish [[entomologist]] notable for pioneering work on the [[forensic entomology|insects of corpses]].
Graëlls was born in [[Tricio]], in the [[La Rioja (autonomous community)|Province of Logroño]]. He died in [[Madrid]] where he had been Professor of [[Zoology]].
[[Image:Graellsia isabellae MHNT male dos.jpg|thumb|Male ''[[Graellsia isabelae]]''.]] [[Image:Sphaeroderma rubidum01.jpg|thumb|The ''[[Sphaeroderma rubidum]]'' was described by Graells in 1858 (Image ©Entomart.ins)]] The ''[[Graellsia isabellae|Graellsia]]'' genus of moths and the [[Graells's tamarin]]{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}} are named after him. He also identified the Iberian subspecies (''[[Meles meles]] [[Meles meles marianensis|marianensis]]'') of the badger. [[Image:Titimadrid.JPG|thumb|230px|left|Exhibit case in the Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, Madrid, Spain – "Life and work of Graells"]]
{{botanist|Graells}}
==Sources== {{reflist}} * Anonym 1898: Graells, M. de la Paz. ''[[Entomologist's Monthly Magazine]]'' (3) 34
==External links== *[https://archive.is/20130106154721/http://cerezo.pntic.mec.es/mgarc144/marcocientificos/marianopazgraells.html Mariano Paz Graells]
{{Authority control}}
