[[File:HCV genome.png|thumb|HCV genome]]
'''Nonstructural protein 4A''' ('''NS4A''') is a [[viral protein]] found in the [[hepatitis C virus]]. It acts as a [[cofactor (biochemistry)|cofactor]] for the enzyme [[NS3 (HCV)|NS3]].<ref name="pmid9738057">{{cite journal  |vauthors=Beld M, Penning M, van Putten M, etal |title=Hepatitis C virus serotype-specific core and NS4 antibodies in injecting drug users participating in the Amsterdam cohort studies |journal=J. Clin. Microbiol. |volume=36 |issue=10 |pages=3002–6 |date=October 1998 |pmid=9738057 |pmc=105101 |doi= |url=http://jcm.asm.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=9738057}}</ref>

