{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}} {{Use British English|date=February 2014}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Shackleton | image = Shackleton DVD Cover.jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Collector's Edition DVD cover | genre = [[Biography]], [[drama]] | creator = | based_on = | writer = [[Charles Sturridge]] | screenplay = | story = | director = [[Charles Sturridge]] | starring = [[Kenneth Branagh]] | narrated = | theme_music_composer = [[Adrian Johnston (musician)|Adrian Johnston]] | country = [[United Kingdom]] | language = English, [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[German language|German]] | num_episodes = 2 | producer = Selwyn Roberts | editor = Peter Coulson | cinematography = Henry Braham | runtime = 206 minutes | company = | distributor = [[A+E Networks|A&E]] | budget = | network = [[Channel 4]] | first_aired = {{Start date|2002|01|02|df=y}} | last_aired = {{End date|2002|01|03|df=y}} | preceded_by = | followed_by = | website = http://www.channel4.com/programmes/shackleton }}
'''''Shackleton''''' is a 2001 British [[television film]] written and directed by [[Charles Sturridge]] and starring [[Kenneth Branagh]] as explorer [[Sir Ernest Shackleton]]. The film tells the true story of Shackleton's [[Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition|1914 Antarctic expedition]] on the ship ''[[Endurance (1912 ship)|Endurance]]''. The cast includes [[Kevin McNally]], [[Lorcan Cranitch]], [[Embeth Davidtz]], [[Danny Webb (actor)|Danny Webb]], [[Matt Day]] and [[Phoebe Nicholls]] (also the director's wife) as Lady Shackleton. It was filmed in the UK, [[Iceland]] and [[Greenland]]. The film used first-hand accounts by the men on the expedition to retell the story. Shackleton biographer [[Roland Huntford]] was a production advisor.
''Shackleton'' was first broadcast in two parts by [[Channel 4]] in January 2002. In [[North America]] the film was first broadcast by the [[A&E Network]] in April 2002. The film was nominated for seven [[Emmy Awards]],<ref name="emmys"/> six [[BAFTA Awards]],<ref name="bafta"/> and a [[Golden Globe Award]].<ref name="golden-globes"/>
==Plot== The films tells the true story of explorer [[Ernest Shackleton|Sir Ernest Shackleton]] ([[Kenneth Branagh]]) and his [[Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition|1914 Antarctic expedition]] on the ship ''[[Endurance (1912 ship)|Endurance]]''. The story begins with him planning the expedition and finding [[Sponsor (commercial)|sponsors]], particularly [[James Key Caird|Sir James Caird]]. Shackleton's goal is to drive [[Dog sled|dog sled teams]] from one side of Antarctica to the other, which would make Britain the first nation to undertake such a trans-continental journey.
Once the expedition is underway, trouble arises due to thick [[sea ice]] and low temperatures. ''Endurance'' becomes trapped and eventually crushed by [[pack ice]]. Shackleton vows to find a way to rescue the men. He undertakes an epic journey across the ice, followed by 800 miles of the [[Southern Ocean]] and then an uncharted mountain range on [[South Georgia Island]]. He finds a [[whaling]] station from which rescue parties are sent to collect his entire [[shipwreck]]ed crew. The otherwise failed expedition is made famous for every crew member surviving despite insurmountable odds.
==Cast== (In Order of Appearance) * [[Kenneth Branagh]] as [[Ernest Shackleton|Sir Ernest Henry Shackleton]] * [[John Grillo]] as Franks * [[Phoebe Nicholls]] as Emily Shackleton * [[Eve Best]] as Eleanor Shackleton * [[Mark Tandy (actor)|Mark Tandy]] as Frank Shackleton * Cicely Delaney as Cecily Shackleton * Christian Young as Raymond Shackleton * [[Embeth Davidtz]] as Rosalind Chetwynd * [[Danny Webb (actor)|Danny Webb]] as Perris * [[Lorcan Cranitch]] as [[Frank Wild]] * [[Michael Culkin]] as [[J. P. Morgan, Jr.|Jack Morgan]] * [[Mark McGann]] as [[Tom Crean (explorer)|Tom Crean]] * Abby Ford as Marcie * [[Kevin McNally]] as [[Frank Worsley]] * [[Robert Hardy]] as [[James Key Caird|Sir James Caird]] * [[Pip Torrens]] as [[James McIlroy (surgeon)|James McIlroy]] * Ken Drury as [[Harry McNish]] * [[Matt Day]] as [[Frank Hurley]]
